SIMPLE: suspensory
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Suspensory
<hw>Sus*pen"so*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Suspended; hanging; depending.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fitted or serving to suspend; suspending; <as>as, a
<ex>suspensory</ex> muscle</as>.</def> <rj><au>Ray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a
suspensorium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suspensory</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Suspensory
<hw>Sus*pen"so*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>suspensoir</ets>, <ets>suspensoire</ets>.]</ety> <def>That which
suspends, or holds up, as a truss</def>; specifically <fld>(Med.)</fld>,
<def>a bandage or bag for supporting the scrotum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Suspicable</ent>⟦br⟧
